Johannesburg - The ANC Women’s League has stopped short of saying that the party’s newly elected deputy president David Mabuza and secretary general Ace Magashule betrayed them. Magashule and Mabuza were central in the campaign for former African Union Commission chairperson Nkosazana Dlamini Zuma to become the ruling party’s leader. But this failed after Deputy President Cyril Ramaphosa won the race. On Monday the leadership of the league blamed Dlamini’s Zuma’s failed bid on patriarchy and betrayal. They however said they would rally behind Ramaphosa. The commitment to support Ramaphosa came amid fears that the Women’s League was due to challenge the election outcomes. 
